<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
The size of this species in Macau ranges 24-31 mm in total length and 5-7 mm in maximum width. Adults are active during the hottest part of the day during May-June and have been observed while feeding on flowers of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Acronychia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acronychia pedunculata" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pedunculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Acronychia pedunculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Psychotria serpens" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Psychotria serpens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prain" authorityYear="1898" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dalbergia benthamii" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benthamii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Dalbergia benthamii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Syzigium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Syzigium buxifolium" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="buxifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Syzigium buxifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(RP pers. obs.). In nearby Hong Kong, larvae of this species have been recorded boring into the wood of citrus plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). More specifically, host plants include 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus aurantifolia" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="aurantifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Citrus aurantifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. aurantium" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">C. aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. limonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="limonia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">C. limonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. microcarpa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="microcarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">C. microcarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. reticulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">C. reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swingle" authorityYear="1915" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Fortunella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fortunella margarita" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="margarita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Fortunella margarita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Duffy, EAJ" journalOrPublisher="British Museum, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B34" refString="Duffy, EAJ, 1968. A monograph of the immature stages of Oriental timber beetles (Cerambycidae). British Museum (Natural History), London, [viii +] 434 pp. [198 figs, 18 pls]" title="A monograph of the immature stages of Oriental timber beetles (Cerambycidae). British Museum (Natural History), London, [viii +] 434 pp. [198 figs, 18 pls]" year="1968">Duffy 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Makihara, H" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of FFPRI" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="95 - 110" refId="B96" refString="Makihara, H, Mannakkara, A, Toshihiko Fujimura, T, Ohtake, A, 2008. Checklist of longicorn coleoptera of Sri Lanka (1): Vesperidae and Cerambycidae excluding Lamiinae. Bulletin of FFPRI 7 (2): 95 - 110" title="Checklist of longicorn coleoptera of Sri Lanka (1): Vesperidae and Cerambycidae excluding Lamiinae." volume="7" year="2008">Makihara et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
